re also reflected on the embedded page. The reason I would find something like this useful is because in many cases, I create a set of instructions such as &quot;how to configure CentOS 7&quot; which includes some very basic configuration settings. Then, after those settings, I may have a separate set of instructions specific to that page such as &quot;how to install Application 1&quot;. Then I may have another page for &quot;how to install Application 2&quot;, etc. If the initial settings for CentOS 7 ever changed, I would need to go into every single application instruction and update them manually. What I am looking to accomplish here is having a single, centralized location for those CentOS 7 instructions where I simply &quot;embed&quot; them in these other pages. This way, if I update the master, those pages are updated dynamically.</div></div></div><div class="postCommentCount"><span class="icon icon-comment"></span><span>1</span></div></a></div><div class="postListItem"><div class="postVotes"><div class="upvote"></div><span>109</span></div><a class="postLink" href="/feature-requests/p/autosave-functionality"><div class="body"><div class="postTitle"><span>Autosave functionality</span></div><div class="statusStale"><div class="uppercaseHeader postStatus inProgress">in progress</div></div><div class="postDetails"><div class="truncate">OR periodical prompts to manually save the page you&#x27;re working on</div></div></div><div class="postCommentCount"><span class="icon icon-comment"></span><span>11</span></div></a></div><div class="postListItem"><div class="postVotes"><div class="upvote"></div><span>155</span></div><a class="postLink" href="/feature-requests/p/action-to-duplicate-pages"><div class="body"><div class="postTitle"><span>Action to duplicate pages</span></div><div class="statusStale"><div class="uppercaseHeader postStatus inProgress">in progress</div></div><div class="postDetails"><div class="truncate">Very useful, if you&#x27;ve many api methods to clone pages and change the parameters.</div></div></div><div class="postCommentCount"><span class="icon icon-comment"></span><span>20</span></div></a></div><div class="postListItem"><div class="postVotes"><div class="upvote"></div><span>17</span></div><a class="postLink" href="/feature-requests/p/do-not-refresh-the-pagescroll-back-to-the-top-after-saving-and-merging"><div class="body"><div class="postTitle"><span>Do not refresh the page/scroll back to the top after saving and merging</span></div><div class="statusStale"></div><div class="postDetails"><div class="truncate">I have some very long pages and whenever I save and merge those pages, the page always refreshes and brings me all the way back up to the top rather than leaving me where I was before. It would be great if it wouldn&#x27;t do this!</div></div></div><div class="postCommentCount"><span class="icon icon-comment"></span><span>2</span></div></a></div><div class="postListItem"><div class="postVotes"><div class="upvote"></div><span>118</span></div><a class="postLink" href="/feature-requests/p/allow-pages-to-be-hidden"><div class="body"><div class="postTitle"><span>Allow pages to be hidden</span></div><div class="statusStale"></div><div class="postDetails"><div class="truncate">When a page has been written but it&#x27;s not quite time to show it, allow the user to hide the page. A workaround is to make a page only a draft—but that doesn&#x27;t work on pages that have already been published.</div></div></div><div class="postCommentCount"><span class="icon icon-comment"></span><span>9</span></div></a></div><div class="postListItem"><div class="postVotes"><div class="upvote"></div><span>197</span></div><a class="postLink" href="/feature-requests/p/resizing-images"><div class="body"><div class="postTitle"><span>Resizing images</span></div><div class="statusStale"><div class="uppercaseHeader postStatus underReview">under review</div></div><div class="postDetails"><div class="truncate">Currently an image covers th